A simple chat room implementation.
Server hosts chatroom and multiple clients can connect.

Server Usage:
./server <PORT>

Client Usage:
./client name <IPADDR> <PORT>

If not provided, PORT and IPADDR will default to values in defaults.h

Each client must have a unique name in order to join the chat room.
Server manages each client with a unique thread. 

Clients can exit chat room sending "/exit"

Files:
  -server.c
    -code for server

  -client.c
    -code for client

  -defaults.h
    -macros w/ default values

  -input.h & input.c
    -functions for getting input from stdin and from socket

  -clientList.h & clientList.c
    -code for clientList struct and clientList vector
